node.text:
Back like I never left! (Read below)

My Instagram account apparently got hacked last week and this was the picture I was planning to post that day. 

It’s from 4 years ago, when my dad was sworn in to be a citizen. 

My dad hadn’t been out of the U.S. in 30 years, and he missed out on so many life events of relatives overseas. 

This was also around the same time that I decided to quit my job and start my law firm from the trunk of my car (while still being around $200k in the hole from law school and real estate debt). 

I made a promise that day, that as soon as I was able, I would take my parents on their first international vacation. 

Three months later, my settlements starting come in and I was able to book a vacation from Atlanta to Singapore, to Malaysia and then NYC. 

The trip was an incredible amount of fun, and we made memories that will last forever.

Three months after that I was debt free (in 2018). 

Three months after that I married the love of my life. 

And since then God has blessed me with way more than I deserve. 

My point of the story is this: take care of those who took care of you first, while you still can!

Alhamdulillah.
